 abstract = {A novel approach based on the Stober method allows breaking of the
symmetry of core-shell systems based on metallic core and metal oxide
shell. By adjusting the proportion of the TiO2 precursor with regard to
the silica precursor, different morphologies of the particles have been
obtained displacing the gold particle from center to eccentric positions
leading to acorn-like and raspberry-like structure.},
